{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4d2b06b8-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20334"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"20334"},"text":"§ 20334.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4d2b06b9-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20334/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter $2,300,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2027 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002174"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002174"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be followed by a period."}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4d2b06ba-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20334/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of funds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Of the amounts appropriated in subsection (a), not less than 80 percent shall be used for grants under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s20333/b"},"text":"section 20333(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4d2b06bb-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20334/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No funds are authorized to be appropriated for a fiscal year to carry out this subchapter unless the aggregate amount appropriated to carry out title II of the Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention Act of 1974 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5611"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 5611","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002175"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002175"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" for such fiscal year is not less than the aggregate amount appropriated to carry out such title for the preceding fiscal year."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4d2b06bc-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tII/s224"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title II, § 224","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4798"},"text":"104 Stat. 4798","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tIV/s40156/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title IV, § 40156(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1923"},"text":"108 Stat. 1923","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/386/dB/tIII/s1302/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–386, div. B, title III, § 1302(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1511"},"text":"114 Stat. 1511","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4/tXI/s1105"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4, title XI, § 1105","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-03-07"},"text":"Mar. 7, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/127/135"},"text":"127 Stat. 135","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/tXIII/s1303"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, div. W, title XIII, § 1303","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/927"},"text":"136 Stat. 927","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4d2b06bd-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4d2b06be-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id4d2b06bf-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention Act of 1974, referred to in subsec. (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/415"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–415","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-09-07"},"text":"Sept. 7, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1109"},"text":"88 Stat. 1109","children":[],"tail":". Title II of the Act was classified principally to subchapter II (§ 5611 et seq.) of chapter 72 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification as subchapter II (§ 11111 et seq.) of chapter 111 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4d2b06c0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s13024"},"text":"section 13024 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4d2b06c1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":" substituted “subchapter $2,300,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2027” for “subchapter $2,300,000 for each of fiscal years 2014 through 2018.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4","children":[],"tail":" substituted “$2,300,000 for each of fiscal years 2014 through 2018.” for “$2,300,000 for each of fiscal years 2001 through 2005.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/386"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–386","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (a) and struck out heading and text of former subsec. (a). Text read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) $750,000 for fiscal year 1996;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) $1,000,000 for fiscal year 1997;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(3) $2,000,000 for fiscal year 1998;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(4) $2,000,000 for fiscal year 1999; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(5) $2,300,000 for fiscal year 2000.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322","children":[],"tail":" amended heading and text of subsec. (a) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this chapter—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) $10,000,000 in fiscal year 1991; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) such sums as may be necessary to carry out this chapter in each of fiscal years 1992, 1993, and 1994.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id4d2b06c2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4d2b06c3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2022 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":" not effective until Oct. 1 of the first fiscal year beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/s4/a"},"text":"section 4(a) of div. W of Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/u